						<p>Damaged. Refers to the remission of marriage tax <hi rend="italic">(kaliyāṇa āyam)</hi> in Tagaḍa-nāḍu, a subdivision of Nigarilichōḻa-maṇḍalam by Vīmappa Nāyakkar, son of Bomma Nāyakkar, an officer ‘who possessed the strength of the king Vishṇuvardhana’.</p>						

